I'm going to talk about being a travel vlogger, which is a job that I've always dreamed of pursuing in the future.
A travel vlogger is someone who visits different places of interrest and documents their experiences through videos, which they then upload to social media platforms. Over time, they can earn money through ads, sponsorships, or support from their followers. Through these videos, viewers can gain first-hand insights into various destinations without having to travel themselves. In addition, vloggers often share useful travel tips, recommendations, and cultural insights, which can help people better prepare for their own trips.
I first became interested in this job about five years ago when I was browsing YouTube in my free time. I happened to come across a video "800 Days Around Vietnam" by Khoai Lang Thang, who is a well-known travel Youtuber in Vietnam. In that video, he showcased breathtaking scenery from different regions he had visited, as well as unique traditions and cultural aspects that I had never known about before. What inspired me the most was the fact that he left his stable 9-to-5 job to follow his passion for traveling. That really motivated me to consider pursuing a similar path.
There are several reasons why I believe this is the perfect job for me. First of all, I'm naturally curious about the way people live their lives in different parts of the world, and I enjoy listening to their stories. I believe this would help me broaden my perspective and gain a deeper understanding of different cultures. Secondly, being a travel vlogger would allow me to be independent and work for myself, which means I could have more freedom and flexibility in my career.
Overall, being a travel vlogger combines my passion for travel, storytelling, and personal freedom, which is why I consider it my ideal job.
